#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:4
msgid "numpy.random.Generator.standard\\_t"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:8
msgid "method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:2
msgid ""
"Draw samples from a standard Student's t distribution with `df` degrees of "
"freedom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:5
msgid ""
"A special case of the hyperbolic distribution.  As `df` gets large, the "
"result resembles that of the standard normal distribution "
"(`standard_normal`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:12
msgid "**df**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:-1
msgid "float or array_like of floats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:12
msgid "Degrees of freedom, must be > 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:18
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:15
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n * "
"k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is "
"returned if ``df`` is a scalar.  Otherwise, ``np.array(df).size`` samples "
"are drawn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:30
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:-1
msgid "ndarray or scalar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:23
msgid "Drawn samples from the parameterized standard Student's t distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:33
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:34
msgid "The probability density function for the t distribution is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:36
msgid ""
"P(x, df) = \\frac{\\Gamma(\\frac{df+1}{2})}{\\sqrt{\\pi df}\n"
"\\Gamma(\\frac{df}{2})}\\Bigl( 1+\\frac{x^2}{df} \\Bigr)^{-(df+1)/2}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:39
msgid ""
"The t test is based on an assumption that the data come from a Normal "
"distribution. The t test provides a way to test whether the sample mean "
"(that is the mean calculated from the data) is a good estimate of the true "
"mean."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:44
msgid ""
"The derivation of the t-distribution was first published in 1908 by William "
"Gosset while working for the Guinness Brewery in Dublin. Due to proprietary "
"issues, he had to publish under a pseudonym, and so he used the name Student."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:50
msgid "References"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:51
msgid "Dalgaard, Peter, \"Introductory Statistics With R\", Springer, 2002."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:53
msgid ""
"Wikipedia, \"Student's t-distribution\" https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Student's_t-distribution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:58
msgid "[Rb7c952f3992e-1]_, [Rb7c952f3992e-2]_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_t:61
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:3
msgid ""
"From Dalgaard page 83 [Rb7c952f3992e-1]_, suppose the daily energy intake "
"for 11 women in kilojoules (kJ) is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:9
msgid ""
"Does their energy intake deviate systematically from the recommended value "
"of 7725 kJ? Our null hypothesis will be the absence of deviation, and the "
"alternate hypothesis will be the presence of an effect that could be either "
"positive or negative, hence making our test 2-tailed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:14
msgid ""
"Because we are estimating the mean and we have N=11 values in our sample, we "
"have N-1=10 degrees of freedom. We set our significance level to 95% and "
"compute the t statistic using the empirical mean and empirical standard "
"deviation of our intake. We use a ddof of 1 to base the computation of our "
"empirical standard deviation on an unbiased estimate of the variance (note: "
"the final estimate is not unbiased due to the concave nature of the square "
"root)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:30
msgid ""
"We draw 1000000 samples from Student's t distribution with the adequate "
"degrees of freedom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:38
msgid ""
"Does our t statistic land in one of the two critical regions found at both "
"tails of the distribution?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:44
msgid ""
"The probability value for this 2-tailed test is about 1.83%, which is lower "
"than the 5% pre-determined significance threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.standard_t.rst:47
msgid ""
"Therefore, the probability of observing values as extreme as our intake "
"conditionally on the null hypothesis being true is too low, and we reject "
"the null hypothesis of no deviation."
msgstr ""

